<TITLE> Police pick up 3 Tahrir men </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 5(bdnews24.com)  The police on Friday captured three Hizb-ut Tahrir members distributing leaflets in the capital. Officer-in-charge of Paltan Police Station, Mohammad Mujibur Rahman, told reporters that they arrested Nader Zamil Chowdhury at the eastern gate of Baitul Mokarram mosque distributing leaflets. He is a first year student of statistics in Dhaka University. He said, distribution of leaflets in the name of a banned organistion like Hizb-ut Tahrir is against the law. "Preparation is underway to file a case against him." The government banned Hizb-ut Tahrir towards the end of 2009. A sub-inspector at New Market police station, Rasul Ahmed Nizami said they arrested Nader Zamil Chowdhury distributing leaflets of the banned organisation in front of New Market station mosque. Chowdhury is a fourth year accounting student in Dhaka College. A sub-inspector at Dhanmandi police station, Alamgir said they arrested a student of ICMAB, Riazul while distributing leaflets in front of the Baitul Aman mosque. Police conducted drives at the houses of the three they had picked up and filed cases against them under anti-terrorism act. bdnews2
